name: Arlene Phillips
summary: Dame Arlene Phillips, at 80, continues to make headlines. She recently received a standing ovation and her first Olivier Award for Best Theatre at the age of 80. Phillips has expressed her disappointment over being fired from Strictly Come Dancing by the BBC. She has also been a vocal advocate for increased funding for dance in the Olivier Awards. Phillips' career highlights include being honored with another standing ovation after winning an Olivier Award for her role in Guys and Dolls. Her journey began with a desire to immerse herself in dance as an escape from her surroundings. Phillips' achievements have been widely recognized, with one notable moment being Sarah Snook's "chicken" performance at the Olivier Awards. However, Sunset Boulevard emerged as the biggest winner at the awards, despite the presence of several celebrities in the nominations.

name: SRH vs RCB
summary: On April 15, 2024, the 30th match of the IPL 2024 took place in Bengaluru between the Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB) and the Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH). The match was filled with record-breaking performances. SRH broke their own record for the highest total in the tournament's history, scoring an astonishing 287 runs in 20 overs. Travis Head played a pivotal role, scoring the second fastest century in IPL history (39 balls). Despite a valiant effort from Dinesh Karthik, who scored 83 runs, RCB fell short in their chase. The match ended with the highest aggregate score (341) ever recorded in a T20 match.
